I"ú<p>The image files of <a href="https://www.favicon-generator.org/about/">Favicons</a> are placed in <code class="highlighter-rouge">assets/img/favicons</code>. You may need to replace them with your own. So letâ€™s see how to customize these Favicons.</p>

<p>Whit a square image (PNG, JPG or GIF) in hand, open the site <a href="https://www.favicon-generator.org/"><em>Favicon &amp; App Icon Generator</em></a> and upload your original image.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/sample/upload-image.png" alt="upload-image" /></p>

<p>Wait a moment for the website to generate icons of various sizes automatically.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/sample/download-icons.png" alt="download-icons" /></p>

<p>Download the generated package and extract the contents to cover all files in folder <code class="highlighter-rouge">assets/img/favicons</code>, but except the following two:</p>

<ul>
  <li>browserconfig.xml</li>
  <li>manifest.json</li>
</ul>

<p>At last, rebuild the site so that the icon becomes your custom edition.</p>

